<Author>kez556
<Content>Cheap  After reading some of the reviews for this hotel i had to come back and leave one of my own. we arrived in Amsterdam at 10am it took us 10 minutes to find the hotel and we were allowed to check in early great.Yes the rooms are a bit dated and there is that smell of cannabis in the air but hey your in the dam. overall the rooms were clean, warm and with a 24 hour reception its everything you need for a great base to explore this fantastic city, you are literally with in 5 minute walking distance to everything.The Grasshopper is four doors away.The staff were really helpful they even wake you up an hour and a half before check out time also as we had a late flight home they allowed us to leave our bags in the office until later in the day. The only downside for us were the stairs very steep and windy but again this is just one of the quirky things about all places in AmsterdamI would absolutely recommend this hotel it does what is says cheap and central great for happy days in Amsterdam 
