<Author>Neats1966
<Content>You get what you pay for - clean but not cheerful! The location of the Beursstraat is fabulous it is situated one street behind the start of the RLD, within seconds of leaving the hotel you are in the heart of the RLD. But it really is a budget hotel, and not a hotel to have any expectations of! If you are not bothered where you stay or what you stay in and just want to get your head down for the night then the beursstraat will just about be okay!  despite some of the earlier reviews I did not see any vermin, or get bitten. I have listed what I consider to be the good and bad points of the hotel and hope these will help anyone decide whether or not the Beursstaat is for them!Good points !!1) Clean sheets, pillow case, shower and toilet.2) Can leave luggage after check out, until departure time.3) 24 hour reception4) Location5) Cost - 拢44 for one night - 2 people 6) Pleasant  helpful reception staff.Not so good points!!!1) Hotel possibly on par with a hostel.2) Rooms shabby  run down3) Only enough hot water for one person to shower, soon runs cold4) No heating in rooms, I was so cold I had to sleep in jeans and jumper!5) Rooms and landing areas stink of dope and tobacco.6) Blankets/Bed throws - I doubt have been washed for years.7) Towels provided - 2 face towels, clean but well worn and tatty.8) Some nice person coughing and clearing their throat excessively early in the morning and spitting out of their bedroom window!!!!! (doubt you'd get that at the ritz!)I certainly wouldnt want to pay a lot of money for a one night stay, after all it is only a bed for the night, but you do get what you pay for and personally I wish I'd paid that little bit more, I am sure had I done so the whole experience would have been much nicer. I wouldnt stay at the beurstraat again, I'd much sooner pay an extra 拢30/拢40 and stay somewhere a bit nicer. My sister stayed at the Hoksbergen hotel, just off dam square (about a 5 min walk), she paid just over 拢70 for the one night and in comparison although still very basic it was nicer, perhaps not worth 拢70 but having toured her hotel and room, it was considered a much more comfortable environment! Breakfast provided was apparently basic but okay. Like the Beurstraat though, the shower in her hotel soon ran cold and only sufficient for one person to shower, leaving her all soaped up and having to rinse off in cold water! But if I had to choose out of the two hotels I would much prefer to stay at the Hoksbergen. 
