<Author>cyberpunkgrrl
<Content>Perfect! I was a little worried after reading some of the reviews on here, but after a wonderful stay I had to come back and write a real review!The postiive things: First of all, we had booked a quad room, for a couple and two single people for two nights. We got there an hour before we could check in, but the hotel guys were more than happy to let us leave our luggage there while we went for breakfast (or was it lunch?? *lol*) We got back after 11am, and were told that we could have 2 twin rooms instead of a quad, which was ideal! The rooms were small, yes, but the beds were clean, and we had an ensuite with a lovely hot shower - we were quite prepared to have to share a bathroom but we had our own which was ideal!The peopel there were very helpful - I managed to lock my key in the room ( yes,i know!) and they were happy to come up and let me in with a spare key.It is *perfectly* placed for everything, 5 mins from the station, 5 seconds from the bars and shops and near 2 tram stops (at Centraal and Dam).The negative things:I do admit the stairs are a little steep, but even me with a dodgy knee was able to manage it up 2 flights to the room.Having no food facilities was a bit annoying, as eating out for very meal gets very expensive! Buy/bring cereal and bread and eat it in your room!I would have no qualms whatsoever in staying at this hotel again 
