<Content>Good location, cheap and cheerful Stayed March 07 booked via Internet. The rooms are basic and pillows are a tad lumpy not to mention the stairs are similar to the summit of everest (no lift), but hey its cheap, has plenty of charachter and most importantly is well located. Its a lively area with all the coffee shops, bars, red light district, central station within a few steps from the hotel. Worth getting a day pass from central station to jump on/off metro which is cheap and stops at all the main sights and v cheap. If you want luxury look eleswhere but if you need a place to stay for a couple of days and are on a budget its an ideal base, hot showers and rooms clean although v small. Had a great short break here and the sun was shining...Enjoy !!!! Nikki + Neil G - Manchester 
