<Author>Jonnie77
<Content>Central location but very, Very basic! This hotel is in a good central location backing on to the red light district and a stones throw from centraal station and the rest of the sights and sounds of Amsterdam.Its a very basic hotel no frills, facilities or extras, the rooms are tiny and the ensuite even more so. You are provided with 2 tiny towels and thats about it. There is no storage or hanging space for anything!!You have to navigate some very narrow and steep stairs to get to your rooms.You do leave a key deposit of 10 euros but this is given back upon checking out which is by 10.30a.m. They will happily store your luggage for you in a room if you have a later flight, train etc at no extra cost.Amsterdam itself is an excellent city break, easy to get around, public transport second to none and plenty to see and do, the red light district is certainly an eye opener and worth a walk through both day and night.Drinks can vary in price depending on bar a vodka and coke cost from 5 euros to 9.5 euros so worth checking out the prices.Summing up, the hotel is clean in an excellent location but lacks any extras best suited to those on a strict budget or who just wanna bed for the night. Defo not for anyone who likes their creature comforts 
