<Author>caguilar76
<Content>Dreadful stay at Hotel Beursstraat!!!!!! At first glance from the outside, you'd think that this hotel could be a decent one....NOT! Let me itemize the awful experience my hubby and our friends had experienced during our stay here:1. No lift/elevator. The stairs shoot straight up, one missed step and you'll tumble down the stairs. Their idea of a lower floor is 3 flights of steps up. Seriously!2. The front desk will ask you for a E10 deposit for your key (as if you'd run away with anything worth taking from their hotel - wahahah!).3. The rooms are carpeted, but instead of vacuuming, they hose their carpeted floors down with water leaving your floor wet and muddy and nasty, hence the sick smell of mildew.4. The bathroom has plenty of hot water, but be careful to check if they even wiped the toilet bowl clean before letting you in. Our friends bathroom still had the scent of rotting pee in the bowl.5. The towels they left in our room were still WET!!! twice they did this!! i had to ask for a dry, cleaner and bigger towels from the front desk. 6. Their pillows...blechh!!! i had never seen a pillow turned brown from drool stain. Make sure you ask for a fresh pillow case to at least have some protection from nastiness. 7. Their walls are paper thin and you can practically hear people farting or belching from the next door. 8. Although their sign says drugs are not allowed inside the hotel, you'll see smoke and smell dope the moment you step into the front lobby..ironic.9. Make sure you lock your windows before you leave your room. Their windows are huge and are easily accessible from the other guest rooms. So, watch out.10. There's a heater inside the room that somehow turns on by itself, it's scary if you ask me, a heater that's turned on and a wet carpet is not a good combo. 
