<Author>Amanda+Jaime
<Content>Refused to stay! With expectations of a simple hotel with a bed and bathroom just to basically sleep in, after 10 minutes we had organised alternative accomodation. As two young Australian girls just touring around Europe we didn't expect much on our budget. we were greeted by the desk staff who found the cartoon on the tv a much higher priority then us arriving to book in. We were treated as though we were more of an inconvenience especially considering we had booked online, and were then ordered (not asked) to pay a deposit for the key. As we walked up the stairs we still remained optimistic that this hotel would be quaint but safe. However, once opening the door to our room we immediately felt unsafe. There was a stale smell coming from the bathroom and the smell of dope was overpowering. (which is expected in Amsterdam but a simple open window could have prevented this) UNTIL we opened the window. we realised that our window opened on to what we think is the roof of the reception below, as did the room across from us. Which we in fact could have walked straight into, hence we felt even more unsafe. We proceeded to actually open the bathroom door to try and air the room. Only to realise that part of the smell was caused by the fact that the toilet had not been flushed. Without sounding like a princess, the smell was so bad that we felt immediately ill. Moving on to the beds, we had a twin room, which meant two tiny beds. They looked dirty, uncomfortable and one of them actually leant against the heater. At the end overall I would never recommend this hotel and have actually made this comment to try and stop other people being put in the same predicament as we were. All I can say is be careful when booking online. 
